# Installed tools (dotfiles stack)

When suggesting shell commands, prefer these tools—they are installed on this machine.

| Tool | Use for | Example |
|------|---------|--------|
| **eza** | Listing files (ls replacement) | `ls`, `ls -la`, `ls -T` |
| **zoxide** | Smart cd by name | `z proj`, `z ~/code/foo` |
| **bat** | View files with syntax highlight | `bat file.sh`, `bat -l json file.json` |
| **rg** / ripgrep | Search in files | `rg "pattern"`, `rg -t py "import"` |
| **fd** | Find files | `fd "*.py"`, `fd name` |
| **watch** | Run command repeatedly | `watch -n 2 'git status'` |
| **fzf** | Fuzzy find (Ctrl+R in shell) | History search, `**` + Tab for files |
| **lazygit** | Git TUI | `lazygit` |
| **lazydocker** | Docker TUI (containers/images/logs/stats) | `lazydocker` |
| **delta** | Git diff pager (auto) | Used by git diff / lazygit |
| **gh** | GitHub CLI | `gh pr list`, `gh repo clone org/repo` |
| **gwtree** | Git worktree + uv + lazygit (subcommands) | `gwtree my-feature` (folder+branch same), `gwtree my-feature -f` (branch `feature/my-feature`), `gwtree feat sc-123 desc`, `gwtree from main hotfix`, `gwtree --help` |
| **dotfiles** | Manage the ~/.dotfiles repo | `dotfiles update`, `dotfiles status`, `dotfiles log`, `dotfiles edit`, `dotfiles doctor`, `dotfiles rollback`, `dotfiles --help` |
| **mole** | SSH tunnels | Port forwarding / reverse tunnels |
| **tmux** | Sessions/panes | `tmux new -s dev`, `tmux attach` |
| **tree** | Directory tree | `tree -L 2` |
| **aws** | AWS/S3 (if installed) | `aws s3 ls`, `aws s3 cp` |

- Shell: **zsh** with Oh My Zsh, Powerlevel10k, zsh-autosuggestions, zsh-syntax-highlighting.
- Terminal: **Ghostty** or **iTerm2**. macOS may have **yabai**, **skhd**, **sketchybar**.
- **`~/.zshrc.local`**: never-tracked, never-touched file for work-specific shell config (exports, aliases, AWS helpers). Auto-sourced by the dotfiles managed block — survives every `dotfiles update`. When the user needs to add machine-specific config, put it there, not in `~/.zshrc`.
- **`dotfiles doctor`**: run when things feel broken after an update; prints PASS/WARN/FAIL for managed block, snippet syntax, Brewfile sync, AWS profile keys, opal CLI shebang, repo status.
- **`dotfiles rollback`**: every install/update takes a timestamped backup of `~/.zshrc`; this restores the most recent one (use `--list` to see all, `-y` to skip confirmation).
